			      MOTIVATION

Whilst   porting   and   enhancing   AnUUCP   -   a   UUCP    mail/news
package for Anubis   BBS  -,  I  noticed  that  Anubis  used  C++-style
comments (//) in so-called "ANSI-C" include  files.  These  //-comments
annoyed GCC  very much  if  it was told to compile ANSI-C. So I decided
to enhance and release cxxc, a simple tool that  had  slumbered  on  my
hard disk for almost a year now.



			INTRODUCTION - FEATURES

Cxxc can automatically convert C++-style comments // in C
source files into C-style comments /* ... */.

Cxxc can strip all C++/C-style comments from source files.

Cxxc uses buffered I/O to speed things up.

Cxxc is pure and can be made resident.

Cxxc comes along with source. See Licence for details.

Cxxc is written in Ansi-C, thus portable. @{"Contact author" link "AUTHOR" 0}  if  you  want
the source.
@endnode

