INSTALLATION

  - copy cxxc to C: or anywhere else in your command search path

OPTIONAL

  - copy cxc to S: or anywhere else in your script search path

  - make cxxc resident. See your AmigaDOS manual, command "RESIDENT"
  for details.



USING CXXC

  cxxc CANNOT be started from Workbench and will refuse to work then.



  cxxc [<option>] <infile> [<outfile>]

  Cxxc reads infile, converts C++- to C-style comments and  writes  the
  changed file to outfile. Outfile defaults to stdout.

  Options are not case sensitive.

  The only supported option is

  -s which tells cxxc to STRIP all C- and C++-style comments.

     Default is to convert C++-style comments to  C-style.  cxxc  takes
     quotation marks into regard. Comments must not be nested (which is
     the default in C).

  WARNING! Commenting out options in C source files is very common. Use
  the  -s  option  with  great  care  in  order  not  to lose important
  information.

  Any other options will simply be ignored WITHOUT NOTICE.



USING CXC

  cxc <file>

  converts C++-style comments to C-style comments. It is mainly cxxc to
  a temporary file and copy back over the original file which is lost.
